cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SY, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with a new algorithm for sampling from probability distributions, which is a common topic in machine learning and statistics. The use of mirror descent and the analysis of convergence rates suggest that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The numerical methods used in the paper also suggest a possible categorization under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The study of the Cox-Ingersoll-Ross process and the analysis of the dynamics suggest a possible categorization under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the use of the algorithm for sampling from Dirichlet posteriors suggests a possible categorization under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
